# GitHub Agent Disclaimer

When posting any comment or message to GitHub on behalf of the user (issue comments, PR comments, review comments, discussion posts), **always** include an agentic disclaimer line at the top of the comment body.

The disclaimer must be the first line, formatted as a blockquote:

```
> *Posted by AI agent on behalf of @{username} — not written directly by a human*
```

Replace `{username}` with the authenticated GitHub user's login.

**Applies to:** all GitHub comments posted via API (`POST`/`PATCH` to issues, pulls, discussions).
**Does not apply to:** PR descriptions (the body of `gh pr create` or the PR body itself).

If a skill already defines its own disclaimer (eg the autonomous PR review skill), use that skill's wording instead — don't double up.
